Right_rally"}
{"title_page": "T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n|  name    =  T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas, S.A.\n|  logo    = Tecnicas Reunidas logo.svg\n|  logo_size =\n|  type    =  [[S.A. (corporation)|Sociedad An\u00f3nima]] \n| traded_as  = {{BMAD|ES0178165017|TRE}}\n|  foundation      =  1959\n|  location        =  [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n|  key_people      =  [[Jos\u00e9 Llad\u00f3 Fern\u00e1ndez-Urrutia]] <small>([[Chairman]])</small>, Juan Llad\u00f3 Arbur\u00faa <small>([[chief executive officer|CEO]])</small>\n|  industry        =  [[Construction]] and [[engineering]]\n|  services        =  Design and construction of [[petrochemical]] facilities, [[power station]]s and [[physical plant|industrial plants]]\n|  revenue         =  {{Increase}} \u20ac4,187 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/recursos/doc/accionistas-e-inversores/cuentas-anuales/presentacion-resultados-anuales-2015.pdf |title=Annual Report 2015 |accessdate=27 May 2016 |publisher=T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas |language=English}}</ref>\n|  operating_income  = {{Decrease}} \u20ac86 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  net_income      =  {{Decrease}} \u20ac62.2 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  assets          =  {{Increase}} \u20ac3,613 million <small>(end 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  equity          =  {{Increase}} \u20ac397 million <small>(end 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  num_employees   =  8,820 <small>(average, 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  homepage        =  [http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/en www.tecnicasreunidas.es]\n}}\n'''T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas, S.A.''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8teknikas rew\u02c8ni\u00f0as}}, meaning \"Gathered Techniques\"), or '''TRSA''', is a [[Spain|Spanish]]-based [[general contractor]] which provides [[engineering]], [[procurement]] and [[construction]] of [[physical plant|industrial]] and [[power station|power generation]] plants, particularly in the [[Petroleum industry|oil and gas]] sector. Since April 2008, the company has been part of the Spanish [[large-cap]] [[IBEX 35]] [[stock index]].\n\nTRSA is the primary holding company for a group of companies capable of providing several different integrated services for [[turnkey]] projects worldwide. Since 1959, the TRSA group of companies has designed and built over 1000 industrial plants worldwide. International projects account for 70% of the company's annual turnover, mainly in [[Latin America]] and [[China]].<ref>[http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/english/index.asp TR Group, Introduction]</ref> The firm has also moved increasingly into the [[Middle East]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.arabnews.com/?page=9&section=0&article=71592&d=17&m=10&y=2005|title=Tecnicas Reunidas: An EPC Company Focusing on ME|date=12 October 2005|work=[[ArabNews]]|accessdate=2009-02-16}}</ref> and in January 2009 was awarded a $1.2 billion contract to develop two [[Onshore (hydrocarbons)|onshore]] fields in the [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]] for a subsidiary of [[ADNOC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/oilRpt/idUKLP67366820090125|title=Tecnicas Reunidas, partner win $1.2 bln UAE oil deal|last=Webb|first=Simon|date=25 January 2009|work=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=2009-02-16}}</ref>\n\n==Organization==\nThe business divisions of TRSA are [[Petroleum|oil and gas]], [[power generation]] and [[infrastructure]]s.\n\nThe areas of activity covered by TRSA's companies are: the [[petrochemical industry]], [[heat transfer]], [[cogeneration]] and [[renewable energies]], [[fertilisers]] and [[inorganic chemistry]], [[environmental engineering]], [[iron]] and [[steel]] plants, [[metallurgy]], [[mining]] and [[hydrometallurgy]].\n\n== Research and development==\n\nSince 1971, the company has its own [[research and development]] division. The company's R&D Centre, located in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], is equipped with laboratory facilities and pilot and demonstration plants designed to be adapted to different process configurations. The R&D division develops new processes and the technological and economical improvement of existing ones, applying techniques and procedures of disciplines such as [[hydrometallurgy]] and [[electrochemistry]]. A fundamental objective is the upscaling from laboratory testing to industrial scale operations.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n*[[List of oilfield service companies]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es}}\n\n{{IBEX-35 companies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tecnicas Reunidas, S.A.}}\n[[Category:Engineering companies of Spain]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in Spain]]\n[[Category:Non-renewable resource companies established in 1959]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Spain]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Madrid]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Madrid Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:IBEX-35]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n|  name    =  T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas, S.A.\n|  logo    = Tecnicas Reunidas logo.svg\n|  logo_size =\n|  type    =  [[S.A. (corporation)|Sociedad An\u00f3nima]] \n| traded_as  = {{BMAD|ES0178165017|TRE}}\n|  foundation      =  1959\n|  location        =  [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n|  key_people      =  [[Jos\u00e9 Llad\u00f3 Fern\u00e1ndez-Urrutia]] <small>([[Chairman]])</small>, Juan Llad\u00f3 Arbur\u00faa <small>([[chief executive officer|CEO]])</small>\n|  industry        =  [[Construction]] and [[engineering]]\n|  services        =  Design and construction of [[petrochemical]] facilities, [[power station]]s and [[physical plant|industrial plants]]\n|  revenue         =  {{Increase}} \u20ac4,187 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/recursos/doc/accionistas-e-inversores/cuentas-anuales/presentacion-resultados-anuales-2015.pdf |title=Annual Report 2015 |accessdate=27 May 2016 |publisher=T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas |language=English}}</ref>\n|  operating_income  = {{Decrease}} \u20ac86 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  net_income      =  {{Decrease}} \u20ac62.2 million <small>(2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  assets          =  {{Increase}} \u20ac3,613 million <small>(end 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  equity          =  {{Increase}} \u20ac397 million <small>(end 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  num_employees   =  8,820 <small>(average, 2015)</small><ref name=\"AR2010\" />\n|  homepage        =  [http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/en www.tecnicasreunidas.es]\n}}\n'''T\u00e9cnicas Reunidas, S.A.''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8teknikas reu\u02c8ni\u00f0as}}, meaning \"Gathered Techniques\"), or '''TRSA''', is a [[Spain|Spanish]]-based [[general contractor]] which provides [[engineering]], [[procurement]] and [[construction]] of [[physical plant|industrial]] and [[power station|power generation]] plants, particularly in the [[Petroleum industry|oil and gas]] sector. Since April 2008, the company has been part of the Spanish [[large-cap]] [[IBEX 35]] [[stock index]].\n\nTRSA is the primary holding company for a group of companies capable of providing several different integrated services for [[turnkey]] projects worldwide. Since 1959, the TRSA group of companies has designed and built over 1000 industrial plants worldwide. International projects account for 70% of the company's annual turnover, mainly in [[Latin America]] and [[China]].<ref>[http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es/english/index.asp TR Group, Introduction]</ref> The firm has also moved increasingly into the [[Middle East]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.arabnews.com/?page=9&section=0&article=71592&d=17&m=10&y=2005|title=Tecnicas Reunidas: An EPC Company Focusing on ME|date=12 October 2005|work=[[ArabNews]]|accessdate=2009-02-16}}</ref> and in January 2009 was awarded a $1.2 billion contract to develop two [[Onshore (hydrocarbons)|onshore]] fields in the [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]] for a subsidiary of [[ADNOC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/oilRpt/idUKLP67366820090125|title=Tecnicas Reunidas, partner win $1.2 bln UAE oil deal|last=Webb|first=Simon|date=25 January 2009|work=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=2009-02-16}}</ref>\n\n==Organization==\nThe business divisions of TRSA are [[Petroleum|oil and gas]], [[power generation]] and [[infrastructure]]s.\n\nThe areas of activity covered by TRSA's companies are: the [[petrochemical industry]], [[heat transfer]], [[cogeneration]] and [[renewable energies]], [[fertilisers]] and [[inorganic chemistry]], [[environmental engineering]], [[iron]] and [[steel]] plants, [[metallurgy]], [[mining]] and [[hydrometallurgy]].\n\n== Research and development==\n\nSince 1971, the company has its own [[research and development]] division. The company's R&D Centre, located in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], is equipped with laboratory facilities and pilot and demonstration plants designed to be adapted to different process configurations. The R&D division develops new processes and the technological and economical improvement of existing ones, applying techniques and procedures of disciplines such as [[hydrometallurgy]] and [[electrochemistry]]. A fundamental objective is the upscaling from laboratory testing to industrial scale operations.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n*[[List of oilfield service companies]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.tecnicasreunidas.es}}\n\n{{IBEX-35 companies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tecnicas Reunidas, S.A.}}\n[[Category:Engineering companies of Spain]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in Spain]]\n[[Category:Non-renewable resource companies established in 1959]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Spain]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Madrid]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Madrid Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:IBEX-35]]\n", "name_user": "Nardog", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingSpanish IPAperdiscussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.or