{"title_page": "Mauro Olivi", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Mauro Olivi\n| image       =\n| fullname    = Mauro Andr\u00e9s Olivi\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1983|3|18|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Jacinto Ar\u00e1uz]], Argentina\n| height      = 1.74 m\n| currentclub = \n| position    = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| youthyears1 = 2000\u20132003\n| youthclubs1 = [[Club Social y Deportivo Liniers|Liniers]]\n| years1      = 2003\u20132005 | clubs1 = [[Club Social y Deportivo Liniers|Liniers]] | caps1 = 94 | goals1 = 61\n| years2      = 2004\u20132005 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Sporting Punta Alta|Sporting]] (loan)   | caps2 = 16 | goals2 = 8\n| years3      = 2005\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[Olimpo de Bah\u00eda Blanca|Olimpo]]           | caps3 = 53 | goals3 = 49\n| years4      = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = [[Audax Italiano]]                          | caps4 = 61 | goals4 = 22\n| years5      = 2011\u20132014 | clubs5 = [[Colo-Colo]]                               | caps5 = 74 | goals5 = 15\n| years6      = 2014\u20132015 | clubs6 = [[Audax Italiano]]                          | caps6 = 23 | goals6 = 3\n| years7      = 2015      | clubs7 = [[Le\u00f3n de Hu\u00e1nuco]]                         | caps7 = 15 | goals7 = 10\n| years8      = 2016      | clubs8 = [[Selangor FA]]                             | caps8 = 25 | goals8 = 9\n| years9      = 2017\u20132018 | clubs9 = [[Liniers de Bah\u00eda Blanca|Liniers]]         | caps9 = 0  | goals9 = 0\n| totalcaps   = 361\n| totalgoals  = 177\n}}\n'''Mauro Andr\u00e9s Olivi''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8maw\u027eo o\u02c8li\u03b2i}}; born 18 March 1983) is an Argentine former professional [[association football|footballer]]. He played as [[Striker (association football)|striker]] or also as an [[attacking midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nOlivi made his youth career at hometown club [[Club Social y Deportivo Liniers|Liniers]], where was promoted to the first-team in 2000, making his career debut in the [[Torneo Argentino A]]. Seasons later, Mauro was loaned to [[Sporting Punta Alta]], scoring eight goals in 16 games during the [[2004-05 in Argentine football|2004\u201305 season]]. After his loan spell at [[Punta Alta]], he was hired by [[Olimpo de Bah\u00eda Blanca|Olimpo]], professional football team of the [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\nHe made his professional debut in a 2\u20130 away win against [[CA Col\u00f3n|Col\u00f3n]] at [[Santa Fe, Argentina|Santa Fe]].\n\n===Audax Italiano===\nOn 6 July 2009, [[Audax Italiano]] signed Olivi for an undisclosed fee. He signed a five\u2013year contract with the [[Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] club.<ref>{{cite news|url=<!-- URL has been invalid since the day it was pasted in here (28 Dec 2011), and I wasn't able to find the article with many Google searches.    mauro-olivi-es-el-nuevo-delantero-de-audax-italiano -->|title=Mauro Olivi es el nuevo delantero de Audax Italiano|date=6 July 2011|work=Audaxitaliano.cl}}</ref> He made his league debut in a 1\u20130 win over [[Santiago Morning]] and his first goal came against [[Uni\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]], in a 4\u22122 away win. In the debut season of Olivi in Chile scored 2 goals in 19 matches.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/footballer/11578/?t=386&s=433|title=Mauro Olivi in the 2009 Chilean Clausura}}</ref>\n\nOlivi got off to a good start for the [[2010 Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n season|2010 season]] scoring twice in Audax's opening league match against [[\u00d1ublense]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/en-guerra-de-goles-nublense-derroto-a-audax-italiano-en-bicentenario-de-la-florida/prontus_nots/2010-01-25/221208.html|title=En guerra de goles \u00d1ublense derrot\u00f3 a Audax Italiano en Bicentenario de La Florida|date=25 January 2010|work=Cooperativa.cl}}</ref> On 15 March, he scored another twice against [[Deportes La Serena]] in a 3\u22121 away win<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/noticias/site/artic/20100315/pags/20100315112056.html|title=Audax Italiano venci\u00f3 a La Serena tras apag\u00f3n|date=15 March 2010|work=La Naci\u00f3n.cl}}</ref> and in the next week scored in the loss against [[Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|Universidad Cat\u00f3lica]] after a very good free kick in the 13th minute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.audaxitaliano.cl/web2/2010/03/22/audax-cayo-ante-universidad-catolica-en-el-monumental/|title=Audax cay\u00f3 ante Universidad Cat\u00f3lica en el Monumental|date=22 March 2010|work=Audaxitaliano.cl}}</ref> He incremented his tally goal during weeks thirteen and fourteen against [[CD Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n|Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n]] and [[CD Palestino|Palestino]]. During FIFA World Cup break, with the likes of [[Mat\u00edas Alejandro Quiroga|Mat\u00edas Quiroga]], [[Emison da Concei\u00e7ao|Roberval]] and [[Cristian Canio]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/cristian-canio-se-convirtio-oficialmente-en-el-nuevo-refuerzo-de-colo-colo/prontus_nots/2010-08-16/152855.html|title=Cristi\u00e1n Can\u00edo se convirti\u00f3 oficialmente en el nuevo refuerzo de Colo Colo|date=16 August 2010|work=Cooperativa.cl}}</ref> all departing from the club in June, Olivi was inserted into the lead striker role. After forming a special relationship with [[Omar Labruna]] \u2014 new manager \u2014 he responded with important goals in games like the 2\u22122 draw with [[CF Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://elgrafico.grupopublimetro.cl/minuto-a-minuto-la-u-con-montillo-y-victorino-juega-con-audax|title=U. de Chile empata 2-2 con Audax y Colo Colo es el campe\u00f3n de invierno|date=22 July 2010|work=El Gr\u00e1fico.cl}}</ref> or the 3\u20131 victory over [[Colo-Colo]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2010/09/12/435793/colo-colo-cae-ante-audax-italiano-y-pierde-el-liderato-del-torneo.html|title=Colo Colo cae ante Audax Italiano y pierde el liderato del torneo |date=12 September 2010|work=Emol.cl}}</ref> He ended the tournament with 18 goals behind midfielder [[Milovan Mirosevic]] with 20 goals, but in the [[Anfp|2010 ANFP awards]], Olivi was awarded with the Golden Ball<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2010/12/13/452633/mauro-olivi-es-premiado-con-el-balon-de-oro-2010-del-futbol-chileno.html|title=Mauro Olivi es premiado con el \"Bal\u00f3n de Oro 2010\" del f\u00fatbol chileno|date=13 December 2011|work=Emol.cl}}</ref> and was included in the Ideal Teams of [[El Gr\u00e1fico]] and of the [[Anfp|ANFP]].\n\nIn the [[2011 Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n season|next season]], Olivi had a very regular start of tournament, being red carded two times in his first games against Cat\u00f3lica<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.audaxitaliano.cl/web2/2011/02/05/audax-cayo-ante-la-uc-en-san-carlos/|title=Audax cay\u00f3 ante la UC en San Carlos|date=5 February 2011|work=Emol.cl}}</ref> and [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.3tv.cl/index.php?m=video&v=17726|title=Uni\u00f3n La Calera venci\u00f3 por 3-1 a Audax Italiano|access-date=2011-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118212852/http://3tv.cl/index.php?m=video|archive-date=2012-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref> but he scored two goals against [[Uni\u00f3n San Felipe]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prensafutbol.cl/noticias-futbol-chileno-primera-a/19501-audax-logro-una-notable-remontada-sobre-san-felipe.html|title=Audax logr\u00f3 una notable remontada sobre San Felipe|date=23 February 2011|work=Prensa F\u00fatbol.cl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.3tv.cl/index.php?m=video&v=17322|title=Audax Italiano venci\u00f3 por 2-1 San Felipe|date=23 February 2011|work=3TV.cl|access-date=31 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118212852/http://3tv.cl/index.php?m=video|archive-date=18 January 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> and [[Santiago Morning]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prensafutbol.cl/noticias-futbol-chileno-primera-a/19572-santiago-morning-y-audax-empataron-en-la-pintana.html|title=Santiago Morning y Audax repartieron puntos|date=27 February 2011|work=Prensa F\u00fatbol.cl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.3tv.cl/index.php?m=video&v=17369|title=Santiago Morning empat\u00f3 2-2 con Audax Italiano|date=27 February 2011|work=3TV.cl|access-date=31 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118212852/http://3tv.cl/index.php?m=video|archive-date=18 January 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> in his first four games. However, he had a poor performance in the tournament scoring 2 goals in 12 appearances.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/footballer/11578/?t=669&s=433|title=Mauro Olivi in the 2011 Chilean Apertura}}</ref>\n\n===Colo-Colo===\nOn 21 July 2011, Claudio Tessa \u2014 Audax's director of football \u2014 confirmed to the web page [[El Mercurio|Emol]] that both clubs reached an agreement for Olivi's transfer to [[Colo-Colo]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2011/07/21/493821/mauro-olivi-se-convierte-en-el-quinto-refuerzo-de-colo-colo.html|title=Mauro Olivi se convierte en el quinto refuerzo de Colo Colo|date=21 July 2011|work=Emol.cl}}</ref> believed to be for around US$1 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.terra.cl/deportes/index.cfm?accion=futbolnacional&id_reg=1706382|title=Colo Colo \"alternativo\" juega ante la UC con dos hombres que valen US$ 2.5 millones|date=9 August 2011|work=Terra.cl}}</ref> In the popular club, he reunited with [[Boris Rieloff]], [[Marco Medel]] and [[Christian Vilches]], his former teammates at Audax. He made his official debut against [[Santiago Wanderers]] at [[Estadio Monumental David Arellano|Estadio Monumental]] as substitute for [[Sebasti\u00e1n Toro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2011/08/08/496858/olivi-y-el-debut-triunfal-de-colo-colo-en-el-clausura-aun-hay-muchas-cosas-por-mejorar.html|title=Olivi y el debut triunfal de Colo Colo en el Clausura: \"A\u00fan hay muchas cosas por mejorar\"|date=8 August 2011|work=Emol.cl}}</ref> In a friendly game for the Copa Gato, Olivi scored the first goal of the 3\u20131 victory to [[CDUC|Universidad Cat\u00f3lica]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://elgrafico.grupopublimetro.cl/colo-colo-vencio-3-1-a-catolica-en-amistoso-en-iquique|title=Colo Colo venci\u00f3 3-1 a Cat\u00f3lica en amistoso en Iquique|date=11 August 2011|work=El Grafico.cl}}</ref> On 23 October, the player scored his first goal for Colo-Colo in a 3\u20131 victory against [[Santiago Morning]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latercera.com/noticia/deportes/futbol/2011/10/688-400753-9-colo-colo-vence-a-santiago-morning-y-llega-con-todo-al-clasico-con-la-u.shtml|title=Colo Colo vence a Santiago Morning y llega con todo al cl\u00e1sico con la \"U\"|date=23 October 2011|work=La Tercera.com}}</ref> which ended a run of 685 minutes of football without a goal. In December 2011, after the club's elimination in the playoffs against [[Cobreloa]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/cobreloa-elimino-a-colo-colo-y-es-finalista-del-clausura/prontus_nots/2011-12-19/152720.html|title=Cobreloa elimin\u00f3 a Colo Colo y es finalista del Clausura|date=20 December 2011|work=Cooperativa.cl}}</ref> was rumours that Olivi would be made available on a free transfer or be loaned due to the striker's poor performances.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2011/12/656-414282-9-mathias-vidangossy-llegara-a-prestamo-a-colo-colo-para-la-temporada-2012.shtml|title=Math\u00edas Vidangossy llegar\u00e1 a pr\u00e9stamo a Colo Colo para la temporada 2012|date=20 December 2011|work=La Tercera.com}}</ref>\n\nAfter several speculations of his departure, [[Ivo Basay]] considered him in the pre\u2013season at [[Temuco]], despite of his possibilities of arrive to a team on loan or also the chance to left Colo-Colo for a [[Brazilian S\u00e9rie A]] club or also an [[Asia]]n side. On 25 February 2012, he scored his side's goal in a 2\u20131 defeat with [[CD Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n|Universidad de Concepci\u00f3n]], generating thus improving his image, after a complicated last season, not obstant Basay failed to call-up Olivi for the next week game in [[Valpara\u00edso]] against Wanderers. However, after the coach's departure, he was chosen by the caretaker [[Luis P\u00e9rez Mu\u00f1oz|Luis P\u00e9rez]] in the starting lineup, recovering his well performances, scoring goals in a 2\u20132 regular phase draw against [[C.S.D. Rangers|Rangers]] and a twice with [[Deportes Iquique]] in the playoffs, being a key player during that instance, after being eliminated by the rival [[CF Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]] in the semifinals.\n\n===Return to Audax===\nIn 2014, he returned to [[Audax Italiano]].\n\n===Le\u00f3n de Hu\u00e1nuco===\nIn 2015, he joined [[Le\u00f3n de Hu\u00e1nuco]].\n\n===Selangor===\nIn 2016, Olivi signed with Selangor from [[Le\u00f3n de Hu\u00e1nuco]], ahead of the upcoming Malaysia Super League season.\n\n===Liniers===\nIn 2017 he joined [[Liniers de Bah\u00eda Blanca|Liniers]].\n\nHe announced his retirement in 2018.\n\n==Controversies==\nOn 31 August 2011, Olivi was arrested by the police after physically assaulting his then girlfriend, dancer Valentina Roth. The events occurred at the footballer's apartment at 3:00 AM, where Roth had a violent discussion with the player. The dancer then called the police and Olivi was arrested, being visited by his club's general manager [[Jaime Pizarro]] at the police station.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.publimetro.cl/nota/espectaculos/mauro-olivi-es-detenido-por-presunta-agresion-a-vale-roth-y-pizarro-lo-visita/xIQkhE!alBHLCnrX0loE/|title=Mauro Olivi es detenido por presunta agresi\u00f3n a Vale Roth y Pizarro lo visita|date=31 August 2011|work=Publimetro.cl}}</ref> The same day that Pizarro visited Olivi it was revealed that the striker would be formalized at the court.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/mauro-olivi-sera-formalizado-por-presunta-agresion-a-la-modelo-valentina-roth/prontus_nots/2011-08-31/101632.html|title=Mauro Olivi ser\u00e1 formalizado por presunta agresi\u00f3n a la modelo Valentina Roth|date=1 September 2011|work=Cooperativa.cl}}</ref> Finally, he was sentenced with the prohibition of approaching Roth in a radius of 100 meters.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/mauro-olivi-tiene-prohibicion-de-acercarse-a-valentina-roth/noticias/2011-08-31/183127.html|title=Mauro Olivi tiene prohibici\u00f3n de acercarse a Valentina Roth|date=1 September 2011|work=La Naci\u00f3n.cl}}</ref>\n\nSome days later, he was linked once again to a TV personality, this time Vaithiare Mu\u00f1oz of [[Chilevisi\u00f3n]]'s youth program Yingo.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/mauro-olivi-versus-valentina-roth-esa-mina-esta-loca-me-cago-la-carrera/noticias/2011-10-21/145703.html|title=Mauro Olivi versus Valentina Roth: \"Esa mina est\u00e1 loca, Me cag\u00f3 la carrera\"|date=1 September 2011|work=La Naci\u00f3n.cl}}</ref> After having been involved in several disciplinary events, Colo Colo's then coach [[Ivo Basay]] marginated him from the squad, which led to speculations that he might leave the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2011/12/656-411567-9-colo-colo-le-raya-la-cancha-a-olivi-por-su-conducta.shtml|title=Colo Colo le raya la cancha a Olivi por su conducta|date=14 December 2011|work=La Tercera.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>1</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Audax Italiano]]\n|[[2009 Torneo Clausura (Chile)|2009\u2013C]]<sup>2</sup>\n|15||2||0||0||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013||15||2\n|-\n|[[2010 